groupId
   artifactId
      version

######################
### USER INTERFACE ###
######################

### Global Configuration

Define multiple Maven repositories that can be accessed by the Jenkins instance:
1. Name
2. Server Base URL
3. Username
4. Password

### Job Configuration

1. Select Maven repository, as defined in the Global Configuration
  1. Main
  2. https://www.mycompany.com/maven
  3. user
  4. password
2. Enter one or more groupIds (seperated by comma)
  Example: com.company.product
3. Enter a pattern which files to transfer
  * TODO: What about include/exclude patterns 
  Example: *.zip

### Build Now

1. Show a dropdown box with all artifactIds from the specified groupIds
  * component1
  * component2
  * ...
  * componentN
2. When an artifactId is selected, populate the version list
  * 1.0.0
  * 1.0.1
  * ...
3. When a version is selected, show a list of files that will be transfered (based on the pattern)
  * abc-1.0.0.zip
  * abc-1.0.0-source.zip
  * abc-1.0.0-doc.zip

### Schedule Build

1. Pass the selection, i.e. a list of artifacts to the Ant script that will be triggered
  -Dartifacts=https://www.mycompany.com/maven/com/company/product/component1/abc-1.0.0.zip,https://www.mycompany.com/maven/com/company/product/component1/abc-1.0.0-source.zip,https://www.mycompany.com/maven/com/company/product/component1/abc-1.0.0-doc.zip
2. The ant script iterates over the list and transfers the files to the project specific desitination

######################
### IMPLEMENTATION ###
######################

1. Use HTTPclient for accessing the Maven repository
Do not use the Nexus or Artifactory REST interfaces because that 
makes us dependent on those repository managers only.

